author: app.com
title: College Corner: Locals spark Rutgers women's soccer
text:
MORE As the wins pile up, so do the messages for Rutgers women’s soccer coach Mike O’Neill.
“I get text messages and emails from all over the country,” he said Monday. “I got one from Sweden today, from a former Rutgers player.”
With a record of 12-2-2, including Sunday’s 1-0 upset of ninth-ranked Penn State at home, O’Neill’s team is the trailblazer for an athletic department still transitioning to the Big Ten Conference.
“Penn State is a measuring stick in the sense of the Big Ten because they’ve won championships and this is the second year we’ve been in there,” O’Neill said. “When it comes to the Big Ten we recognize in order to compete for a championship, we need to have the talent and the mindset that this is the level we need to play at.”
